<article class="container -project" id="content" role="main">
	
<div class="project-hero">
	<img width="2000" height="1333" src="https://calmatters.org/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2019/07/07292019_recycling_AW_sized_03.jpg?fit=2000%2C1333" class="project-hero__image wp-post-image" alt="Two levels of conveyer belts carrying items to be recycled seen from above at greenwaste in San Jose on July 29, ,2019. Photo by Anne Wernikoff/CalMatters" srcset="https://calmatters.org/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2019/07/07292019_recycling_AW_sized_03.jpg?w=2000 2000w, https://calmatters.org/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2019/07/07292019_recycling_AW_sized_03.jpg?w=300 300w, https://calmatters.org/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2019/07/07292019_recycling_AW_sized_03.jpg?w=768 768w, https://calmatters.org/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2019/07/07292019_recycling_AW_sized_03.jpg?w=1024 1024w, https://calmatters.org/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2019/07/07292019_recycling_AW_sized_03.jpg?w=1536 1536w, https://calmatters.org/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2019/07/07292019_recycling_AW_sized_03.jpg?w=460 460w, https://calmatters.org/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2019/07/07292019_recycling_AW_sized_03.jpg?w=321 321w, https://calmatters.org/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2019/07/07292019_recycling_AW_sized_03.jpg?w=780 780w, https://calmatters.org/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2019/07/07292019_recycling_AW_sized_03.jpg?w=858 858w, https://calmatters.org/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2019/07/07292019_recycling_AW_sized_03.jpg?w=794 794w" sizes="(max-width: 2000px) 100vw, 2000px" />
	<div class="container">
		<div class="project-hero__content">
			
			<h1 class="project-hero__title">Seabirds eating plastic. Recyclers struggling. This is what California’s waste crisis looks like</h1>

			
						<p class="project-hero__intro">With China no longer a market for our disposables, the stuff we recycle increasingly winds up in landfills anyway. Localities across California are struggling to cope—and hoping not to undo the decades of work that made household recycling a habit.</p>
			
							<div class="project-hero__caption">

											<svg role="img" class="icon icon--camera" aria-label="camera"><use xlink:href="https://calmatters.org/wp-content/themes/thenewsproject/dist/svg/dist/symbol/svg/sprite.symbol.svg#camera"></use></svg>						<span>Conveyor belts carry the recycling through San Jose-based GreenWaste Recovery, Inc. Photo by Anne Wernikoff for CalMatters, July 29, 2019.</span>
									</div>
					</div>
	</div>
</div>

<nav class="project-navigation">
	<ul>
					<li>
				<a href="https://calmatters.org/projects/california-recycling-plastic-packaging-product-waste-policy/" class="project-navigation__link  -part-1">
					<span class="project-navigation__label">Part 1</span> Tired of plastic junk? California’s recycling bills propose dramatic new rules				</a>
			</li>
						<li>
				<a href="https://calmatters.org/projects/california-recycling-plastics-trash-waste-crisis/" class="project-navigation__link project-navigation__link--active -part-2">
					<span class="project-navigation__label">Part 2</span> Seabirds eating plastic. Recyclers struggling. This is what California’s waste crisis looks like				</a>
			</li>
				</ul>
</nav>

